The paper discusses a visual query system for large-scale tabular datasets, which involves data distribution analysis, space partitioning, locality-sensitive hashing, and summed area table scheme. These techniques are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) to optimize query performance. The paper also emphasizes the importance of flexible visual specifications and user-adjustable granularities, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper mentions the computational complexity of the proposed approach, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
